data.description:
Charming Main-Level Rancher in Prime Location Property Overview: Nestled in a serene neighborhood, this delightful
rancher promises the convenience and comfort of main-level living. The property boasts a well-manicured front yard, setting
the stage for a welcoming ambiance throughout the home. Interior Features: Bedrooms: Two cozy bedrooms, freshly
carpeted, offering a peaceful retreat. Bathroom: A well-appointed full bathroom. Kitchen: A functional kitchen with modern
amenities, including a full-size washer/dryer and a dedicated mechanical closet. Living & Dining Areas: Open and inviting,
these areas seamlessly connect, highlighted by a walkout to a spacious wood deck—ideal for relaxation or entertaining.
Bonus/Family Room: A large, versatile space (non-conforming, converted from a 1-car garage) adaptable to various needs,
whether a family room, home office, or hobby area. Exterior Highlights: Backyard: Experience the beauty of nature in the
privacy of your fenced backyard, adorned with mature trees and offering picturesque mountain views. Wood Deck: A sizable
deck providing a perfect outdoor setting for gatherings or quiet evenings. Location Perks: Proximity to Parks: Just half a
block from Wildflower Park, offering green spaces and recreational activities. Accessibility: Convenient access to major
thoroughfares like Powers and Academy, simplifying travel to the airport, Peterson AFB, and Fort Carson. Neighborhood: A
friendly and welcoming community. Additional Features: Parking: Ample space with extra parking beside the driveway.
Recent Updates: New bedroom carpeting enhances the home's cozy appeal. Invitation to View: This property is a gem,
offering the perfect blend of comfort, convenience, and beauty. Don't miss the opportunity to make it your own.
